Home.description: Frodo and Sam arrive in Mordor with the help of Gollum. A nuMBer of new allies join their former companions to defend Isengard as Saruman launches an assault from his domain.

Home.name: The Scorpion King
Home.description: An assassin, Mathayus, is hired by the leaders of the free tribes to stop Memnon, an evil king, from demolishing their land. The task turns out to be much more dangerous than he had expected.

Home.name: G.I. Joe: Rise of the Cobra
Home.description: Duke and Ripcord join an elite military unit, the G.I.JOE, after they are attacked by an evil organisation, Cobra. The two along with G.I.JOE use next-generation technology to defeat the threat.

Home.name: IB 71
Home.description: An Indian intelligence service must prevent a terrorist attack in this high-stakes Hindi-language thriller. Moments of threat are frequent but fight sequences are restrained with limited injury detail.

2018 also known as Everyone is a Hero, is based on real kerala story and true events in 2018 Kerala floods. It released on May 5, 2023. An Indian Malayalam-language survival thriller film directed by Jude Anthany Joseph, who wrote the screenplay with Akhil P. Dharmajan.

Home.name: Afwaah
Home.description: Afwaah is a 2023 Indian Hindi-language mystery thriller film written and directed by Sudhir Mishra. Produced by Anubhav Sinha and Bhushan Kumar under their respective banners Benaras Media Works and T-Series Films, the film stars Nawazuddin Siddiqui, Bhumi Pednekar and Taapsee Pannu.

Home.name: Odd Thomas
Home.description: Odd, a cook, can see the dead. When a stranger enters his town along with predators that can feed on pain, Odd teams up with his girlfriend and the local sheriff to save the town.

Home.name: Ravanasura
Home.description: ACP Hanumanth Rao, a police officer, investigates a few brutal murders and zeroes in on junior criminal lawyer Ravindra, who, under his goofy exterior, harbours a secret penchant for murder.

Home.name: Detective Chinatown 3
Home.description: Baiqiang Wang and Haoran Liu are back solving mysteries and fighting crime in the third entry in the hugely successful Chinese buddy action-comedy series.

Home.name: Gumraah
Home.description: Gumraah is a 2023 Indian Hindi-language crime thriller film directed by Vardhan Ketkar and produced by T-Series Films and Murad Khetani's Cine1 Studios. The film stars Aditya Roy Kapur, in a dual role along with Mrunal Thakur and Ronit Roy. It is a remake of the 2019 Tamil film Thadam.

Home.name: Viduthalai Part 1
Home.description: Viduthalai, marketed as Viduthalai Part 1, is a 2023 Tamil-language period police procedural crime thriller film written and directed by Vetrimaaran. Produced by Elred Kumar under the banners of RS Infotainment. It is adapted from short story Thunaivan written by Jeyamohan. The film stars Soori and Vijay Sethupathi.

Home.name: Enter Nowhere
Home.description: Three strangers arrive one at a time in a remote cabin, and learn they have been brought together for a reason.

Home.name: Gaslight
Home.description: Gaslight is a 2023 Indian Hindi-language mystery-thriller film, directed by Pavan Kirpalani and produced by Ramesh Taurani and Akshai Puri. The film stars Sara Ali Khan, Vikrant Massey and Chitrangada Singh. It was released on 31 March 2023, on Disney+ Hotstar.

Home.name: Scream VI

Home.description: Unable to remember anything about his life, a man begins regaining consciousness in a new body every 12 hours. Now, he must piece together his identity, all while evading attacks from pursuing agents and dangerous criminals alike.

Home.description: When her mother disappears while on vacation in Colombia with her new boyfriend, June's search for answers is hindered by international red tape. Stuck thousands of miles away in Los Angeles, June creatively uses all the latest technology at her fingertips to try and find her before it's too late. However, as she digs ever deeper, her digital sleuthing soon raises more questions than answers.

Home.name: Sharper
Home.description: Motivations are suspect, and expectations are turned upside down, as a con artist takes on Manhattan billionaires.

Home.name: Barbarian
Home.description: A young woman discovers the rental home she booked is already occupied by a stranger. Against her better judgment, she decides to spend the night but soon discovers there's a lot more to fear than just an unexpected house guest.

Home.name: Kooman
Home.description: A strict police officer moves to a hilly village on the border between Kerala and Tamil Nadu. Events disrupt his life and that of many other people connected to that police station.

Home.name: Lost

Home.name: Knock at the Cabin

Confused, scared and with limited access to the outside world, the family must decide what they believe before all is lost.

Home.name: Pathaan
Home.description: Make. Some. Noise! PATHAAN is here! The high-octane spy thriller 'PATHAAN' starring Shah Rukh Khan, Deepika Padukone and John Abraham, directed by Siddharth Anand is set to release on January 25, 2023. The action spectacle will be released in Hindi, Tamil and Telugu. Celebrate Pathaan with YRF50 only at a big screen near you.

Home.name: The Invitation

Invited by her newfound family to a lavish wedding in the English countryside, Evie's at first seduced by the sexy aristocratic host. However, she's soon thrust into a nightmare of survival as she uncovers twisted secrets about her family history and the unsettling intentions behind their sinful generosity.

Home.name: Luckiest Girl Alive
Home.description: A writer's perfectly crafted New York City life starts to unravel when a true-crime documentary forces her to confront her harrowing high school history and question the choices she made as a teenager.

Home.name: The Pale Blue Eye

Home.name: Glass Onion: A Knives Out Mystery

Home.name: Kiss The Girls
Home.description: A detective travels across town to investigate his niece's kidnapping and hunt for a serial killer called Casanova. A victim who manages to escape from his icy clutches decides to help the detective.

Home.name: Om (Rashtra Kavach Om)

It stars Aditya Roy Kapur, Sanjana Sanghi, Jackie Shroff, Ashutosh Rana, Prakash Raj and Prachee Shah Paandya. The film was released on 1 July 2022.

Navigating the capital's darkened streets, he races to a series of ominous encounters to keep the Vatican from being blown to bits.

Home.name: Kissebaaz
Home.description: Chuttan Shukla, a convict, says he is innocent and narrates the story of Harsh, a young man who is involuntarily dragged into a huge conspiracy involving a mysterious man named Ram Lal.

Home.name: Basic Instinct
Home.description: Detective Nick is tasked with investigating the murder of Johnny Boz. He suspects Johnny's girlfriend Catherine to be responsible for the act. However, things take a turn when he falls for her.

Home.name: Knives out
Home.description: The circumstances surrounding the death of crime novelist Harlan ThroMBey are mysterious, but there's one thing that renowned Detective Benoit Blanc knows for sure -- everyone in the wildly dysfunctional ThroMBey family is a suspect. Now, Blanc must sift through a web of lies and red herrings to uncover the truth.

Home.name: Scoob

Home.name: Cut Off

However, when Amy goes missing on the couple's fifth wedding anniversary, Nick becomes the prime suspect in her disappearance. The resulting police pressure and media frenzy cause the Dunnes' image of a happy union to cruMBle, leading to tantalizing questions about who Nick and Amy truly are.

Home.name: The Da Vinci Code
Home.description: SyMBologist Robert Langdon travels from Paris to London to unravel a bizarre murder. Accompanied by a cryptographer, he soon comes across a religious enigma protected by an age-old secret society.

Home.name: Vettah
Home.description: Two police officers take it upon themselves to investigate the case of a missing actress. They must deal with the criminal who, despite having admitted to the crime, refuses to reveal anything.

Home.name: Sherlock Holmes
Home.description: Detective Sherlock Holmes and his partner, Dr Watson, send Blackwood, a serial killer, to the gallows. However, they are shocked to learn that he is back from the dead and must pursue him again.

Home.name: Enemy

The film features Vishal, Arya, Mirnalini Ravi, and Mamta Mohandas in the lead roles, while Prakash Raj, Thambi Ramaiah, and Karunakaran play supporting roles.

Home.name: Pancharaaksharam

Home.name: Annabelle Comes Home

Home.name: Bees Saal Baad
Home.description: Vijay returns to his hometown only to be warned to stay away due to a vengeful spirit responsible for killing his ancestors. But Vijay decides to investigate the matter and hires a private detective.

Home.name: Murder Mystery

Home.name: The Girl on the Train

Home.name: The Falling

Home.name: Writer

The film stars Samuthirakani, Dileepan and Ineya, and the music is composed by Govind Vasantha

Home.name: Samrat & Co.

Home.name: Iru Mugan

Home.name: Detective Byomkesh Bakshy!
Home.description: Byomkesh, fresh out of college, agrees to investigate the disappearance of Bhuvan, a chemist. Assisted by Bhuvan's son Ajit, Byomkesh links the case to a larger conspiracy that will unsettle Calcutta.

Home.name: Gumnaami

Home.name: Netrikann

Home.name: Maharshi

Home.name: V

Home.name: Hit

Home.name: Pushpa: The Rise (TELUGU)

Home.name: Allahyar and the legend of Markhor
Home.description: Allahyar, a young and mischievous boy living in the northern region of Pakistan, tries to save a Markhor from being illegally hunted by Manu, a ruthless poacher.

Home.name: Motu Patlu - King of Kings
Home.description: Motu and Patlu help Guddu, a circus lion, return to the jungle, which an evil poacher, Narsimha, dominates. The duo teams up with the animals to coMBat him and restore peace.

Home.name: Pokemon: Destiny Deoxys
Home.description: Pokmon: Destiny Deoxys is a 2004 Japanese anime film directed by Kunihiko Yuyama. It is the seventh film in the Pokmon series and the second film released under Pocket Monsters Advanced Generation in Japan.

Home.name: Eight Crazy Nights
Home.description: Davey Stone, a 33-year-old alcoholic, runs into trouble with the law after his wild ways go too far. He is sentenced to community service to reform his bad habits.

Home.name: Monster High: Boo York, Boo York
Home.description: Cleo de Nile invites her boyfriend and other classmates to a party organised by her father while Ghoulia tries to save the Earth from a comet collision.

Home.name: Shabaash Mithu
Home.description: From child prodigy to trailblazer, former Test and ODI captain of India women's national cricket team Mithali Raj becomes a sports icon.

Home.name: Creed III
Home.description: Still dominating the boxing world, Adonis Creed is thriving in his career and family life. When Damian, a childhood friend and former boxing prodigy resurfaces after serving time in prison, he's eager to prove that he deserves his shot in the ring. The face-off between former friends is more than just a fight. To settle the score, Adonis must put his future on the line to battle Damian -- a fighter who has nothing to lose.

Home.name: Champion
Home.description: A former arm-wrestling champion raised in the U.S. returns to South Korea for a tournament that could return him to glory, but he finds his life complicated by the appearance of the biological family he never knew.

Home.name: Azhar
Home.description: Azhar Mohammad, who belongs to a middle class family, becomes an eminent cricketer. However, accusations of match-fixing begin to jeopardise his reputation.

Home.name: Soorma
Home.description: Sandeep, a hockey player, is left paralysed after a gunshot accidentally hits him. He decides to make a comeback to the sport and overcomes his disability to lead the Indian team to victory.

Home.name: Anek
Home.description: Amid turmoil in north-east India, an undercover agent tasked with peace negotiations crosses paths with a tenacious boxer fighting for her dreams.

Home.name: Yeh ballet
Home.description: Discovered by an eccentric ballet master, two gifted but underprivileged MuMBai teens face bigotry and disapproval as they pursue their dancing dreams.

Home.name: Jersey
Home.description: Arjun, a talented but failed cricketer, decides to return to cricket in his late thirties, driven by the desire to represent the Indian cricket team and fulfil his son's wish for a jersey as a gift.

Home.name: A1 Express
Home.description: A young man moves to a new town and falls in love with a hockey player. However, he soon finds himself opposing a corrupt politician's plan to usurp the ground his girlfriend's team practices on.

Home.name: Chak De! India
Home.description: Kabir Khan, a former hockey star, is tainted as someone who betrayed his country. However, he begins coaching the Indian women's national hockey team to prove his loyalty to the nation.

Home.name: Dil Bole Hadippa!
Home.description: Veera, a cricket-crazy Punjabi girl, wishes to enter the men's cricket team to play in the World Cup. She disguises herself as a man but falls in love with her team's coach, Rohan.
On June 25, 1983, the Lord's Cricket Ground witnessed 14 men beat the twice over World Champions West Indies, putting India back onto the cricket world stage.

Home.name: Creed II
Home.description: In 1985, Ivan Drago killed Apollo Creed in a tragic boxing match. Under the guidance of his trainer Rocky, Apollo's son Adonis confronts Drago's son in an ultimate showdown.

Home.name: Panga
Home.description: Jaya, a former Kabaddi world champion, is pushed into making a comeback into the sport by her family. However, she first has to battle her internal conflicts and the expectations society has of her.

Home.name: Rashmi Rocket
Home.description: Rashmi, a small-town girl, overcomes societal barriers and goes on to become a national-level athlete. However, her career hits rock bottom when she is forced to undergo a gender test.

Home.name: Bhaag Milkha Bhaag
Home.description: Milkha Singh, an Indian athlete, overcomes many agonising obstacles in order to become a world champion, Olympian and one of India's most iconic athletes.

Home.name: Mary Kom
Home.description: When Mary Kom encounters a renowned coach in a boxing gym, she shares her boxing aspirations with him and convinces him to teach her. Despite her father's disapproval, she follows her passion.

Home.name: Pele: Birth of a Legend
Home.description: Pele lives in a poor Brazilian neighbourhood and does menial jobs to support his family. However, he continues to hone his powerful footballing skills that eventually make him a national icon.

Home.name: Gold
Home.description: Post independence, Tapan Das, the manager of the Indian hockey team, faces several obstacles as he prepares his team for the upcoming Olympics in the hope of winning a gold medal for the country.

Home.name: Golondaaj
Home.description: During British rule in India, an Indian named Nagendra Prasad Sarbadhikari dared to play the sport of football and challenge the Brits to it.

Home.name: M.S. Dhoni: The Untold Story
Home.description: M S Dhoni, a boy from Ranchi, aspires to play cricket for India. Though he initially tries to please his father by working for the Indian Railways, he ultimately decides to chase his dreams.

Home.name: Sachin: A Billion Dreams
Home.description: Sachin Tendulkar recounts his journey of becoming one of the most famous names in cricket with the help of archival footage, re-enactments and clips of his family, friends and colleagues.

Home.name: Bigil
Home.description: Michael, an aggressive young man, gives up his dream of becoming a footballer after his father's murder. However, a friend convinces him to coach a women's football team and turn his life around.

Home.name: Glory Road
Home.description: Don Haskins creates history by selecting seven African-American players in his basketball team named Texas Western Miners. The team gets criticised by everyone, but they try to win against all odds.

Home.name: Patiala House
Home.description: Gattu loves to play cricket, even though his father hates the sport. After he gets selected to play for an English team, he must choose between his dreams and his father's wishes.

Home.name: Creed
Home.description: Adonis Johnson, the son of heavyweight champion Apollo Creed, eMBraces his legacy as a boxer and seeks mentorship from Rocky Balboa, his father's old friend and rival.

Home.name: Toofaan
Home.description: Toofaan is a 2021 Indian Hindi-language sports drama film directed by Rakeysh Omprakash Mehra and starring Farhan Akhtar as a national level boxer, alongside Mrunal Thakur and Paresh Rawal in supporting roles. The film premiered on 16 July 2021 on Amazon Prime Video.

Home.name: Saina
Home.description: Saina Nehwal, a badminton enthusiast, considers pursuing the sport full-time. When she starts training under an efficient coach, she soon becomes the best and ranks nuMBer one in the sport.

Home.name: King Richard
Home.description: Armed with a clear vision and a brazen, 78-page plan, Richard Williams is determined to write his two daughters, Venus and Serena, into history. Training on tennis courts in Compton, Calif., Richard shapes the girls' unyielding commitment and keen intuition. Together, the Williams family defies seemingly insurmountable odds and the prevailing expectations laid before them.

Home.name: All Things Fall Apart
Home.description: Deon, a football player, while at the pinnacle of his football career, finds his life in serious jeopardy. He sets out to reasseMBle the broken pieces in his life while also battling a lethal disease.

Home.name: Above The Rim
Home.description: Kyle, a high school basketball player, has to choose which team he wants to be a part of in a local tournament- his school team or a team run by a local drug dealer.

Home.name: She Ball
Home.description: On a mission to save his Inglewood, Calif., community centre, a man enlists a talented basketball player to help him win the grand prize in a street ball tournament. Together, they challenge politicians, gangs and stereotypes to save their community.
